WEBVTT

00:04.460 --> 00:12.600
Oxford Bookworms Stage 1, published by FLTRP Copyright Oxford University

00:12.600 --> 00:14.300
Press 2009

00:15.900 --> 00:21.700
Mary Queen of Scots, by Tim Vickery, read by Claire

00:21.700 --> 00:22.340
Willy

00:26.300 --> 00:36.840
Chapter 1, Fothering Gay My name is Bess Curl, but

00:36.840 --> 00:38.960
this is not my story.

00:40.060 --> 00:45.020
It is the story of my Lady Mary, Queen of

00:45.020 --> 00:50.380
Scots. She wrote the story, and then she gave

00:50.380 --> 00:54.740
it to me. I am going to give it to

00:54.740 --> 01:02.980
her son. She began the story a week ago. It

01:02.980 --> 01:03.680
was January

01:06.360 --> 01:11.860
1587, and we sat here in our cold room, in

01:11.860 --> 01:15.540
Fothering Gay Castle, in the north of England.

01:17.440 --> 01:22.900
We couldn't see much from the window. One or two

01:22.900 --> 01:28.700
houses, a river, some trees, some horses,

01:29.200 --> 01:36.300
and a road. That's all. The road goes to London,

01:37.540 --> 01:40.240
the home of Queen Elizabeth of England.

01:42.140 --> 01:47.540
Mary sat with her little dog in her hands, and

01:47.540 --> 01:53.900
watched it all day long. No one came along the

01:53.900 --> 02:04.220
road. Nothing happened. I watched Mary unhappily. Please your majesty,

02:05.360 --> 02:06.920
come away from that window,

02:06.920 --> 02:12.860
I said. It doesn't help. No one is going to

02:12.860 --> 02:19.620
come. Queen Elizabeth can't do it. Queens don't

02:19.620 --> 02:27.420
kill queens. Don't they, Bess? Mary said, then why are

02:27.420 --> 02:32.540
we here in this prison? Why am I not free?

02:33.940 --> 02:40.120
Why, your majesty? Because Queen Elizabeth is afraid of you.

02:41.620 --> 02:48.540
That's right, Mary said. She's afraid of me, and she

02:48.540 --> 03:02.520
hates me too. She hates me because I am

03:02.520 --> 03:07.100
afraid of you. And because many people, good Catholic people

03:07.100 --> 03:10.140
in England, France, Scotland,

03:10.980 --> 03:15.460
Spain, say that I, Mary, and the true queen of

03:15.460 --> 03:20.660
England, not Elizabeth. And Elizabeth has

03:20.660 --> 03:26.360
no children, so when she is dead, my son, James,

03:27.060 --> 03:31.420
she came away from the window and stood

03:31.420 --> 03:39.060
in front of me. James, she said quietly, my son,

03:39.780 --> 03:45.920
does he think about me sometimes? He

03:45.920 --> 03:50.100
was only ten months old when I last saw him.

03:51.240 --> 03:58.240
It is nearly twenty years. Of course he thinks

03:58.240 --> 04:03.860
about you, your majesty, I said. You write to him

04:03.860 --> 04:07.120
often. How can he forget his mother?

04:08.940 --> 04:16.260
Then why doesn't he write to me? Mary asked. Does

04:16.260 --> 04:19.160
he want me to stay here in an English

04:19.160 --> 04:26.120
prison? No, of course not your majesty. But he has

04:26.120 --> 04:29.720
a lot of work, your majesty. He is the

04:29.720 --> 04:35.120
king of Scotland, and he is not the king of

04:35.120 --> 04:40.740
Scotland best, she said. Not before I am dead.

04:41.600 --> 04:48.880
Remember that. No, your majesty. Of course not. But perhaps

04:48.880 --> 04:51.940
people tell him things that are untrue.

04:53.120 --> 05:01.000
You know what people say. Perhaps he thinks you killed

05:01.000 --> 05:05.980
his father. Mary's face went white.

05:07.160 --> 05:11.260
She was very angry, and for a minute I was

05:11.260 --> 05:17.180
afraid. She said, you know that's a lie,

05:17.180 --> 05:23.000
best. It is a lie. I did not kill James's

05:23.000 --> 05:29.000
father. I knew nothing about it. I know that,

05:29.480 --> 05:36.320
your majesty. But perhaps James doesn't know it. He hears

05:36.320 --> 05:41.120
so many lies all the time. He needs

05:41.120 --> 05:47.200
to know the true story. Why don't you write and

05:47.200 --> 05:55.180
tell him? Mary sat down slowly. She looked old

05:55.180 --> 06:03.820
and tired. All right, best. She said, give me a

06:03.820 --> 06:09.320
pen, please. I'm going to write to James and tell

06:09.320 --> 06:14.180
him the true story. You can give it to him

06:14.180 --> 06:21.340
when I'm dead. Dead, your majesty. Don't say that.

06:22.120 --> 06:28.220
You aren't going to die. Her old, tired eyes looked

06:28.220 --> 06:34.340
at me. Yes, I am, best. You know what is

06:34.340 --> 06:34.560
going

06:34.560 --> 06:39.880
to happen? One day soon, a man is going to

06:39.880 --> 06:45.400
bring a letter from Queen Elizabeth, and then her men

06:45.400 --> 06:51.680
are going to kill me. But before I die, I

06:51.680 --> 06:57.060
would like to write to my son, James. I want

06:57.060 --> 06:58.400
to tell him

06:58.400 --> 07:03.900
the story of my life. So give me a pen,

07:04.500 --> 07:12.740
please. I gave her a pen. This is what she

07:12.740 --> 07:13.000
wrote.

07:33.260 --> 07:45.620
Chapter 2 France. Dear James, very soon I am going

07:45.620 --> 07:51.420
to die and meet my God. Before I die,

07:51.420 --> 07:56.380
I want to write the true story of my life

07:56.380 --> 08:04.920
for you. Everything that I write here is true. I

08:04.920 --> 08:05.240
cannot

08:05.240 --> 08:11.880
lie to you or to God. Please believe that, James.

08:12.960 --> 08:18.980
It's important to me. My father died when I was

08:18.980 --> 08:23.900
one week old. So I was the queen of Scots

08:23.900 --> 08:30.400
when I was a baby. At first, I lived with

08:30.400 --> 08:31.620
my mother in

08:31.620 --> 08:37.160
Scotland, and then when I was five, I went to

08:37.160 --> 08:43.300
France. My mother was French, but she stayed in

08:43.300 --> 08:50.620
Scotland, and died there. I went to France to marry

08:50.620 --> 08:56.220
the king of France's son. His name was Francis,

08:57.440 --> 09:03.920
and he was one year younger than me. In 1559,

09:04.360 --> 09:09.620
his father died, so Francis was king.

09:11.140 --> 09:15.700
Then I was queen of France and queen of Scotland

09:15.700 --> 09:23.720
too. I was very happy in France. Francis, my husband,

09:24.240 --> 09:29.100
was like a little brother to me. I think he

09:29.100 --> 09:33.920
loved me, but he was very young, and he was

09:33.920 --> 09:34.620
often ill,

09:35.420 --> 09:42.720
and then in 1560, he died. He was 16 years

09:42.720 --> 09:49.800
old. When he died, I was very unhappy, and my

09:49.800 --> 09:50.560
life was

09:50.560 --> 09:56.240
very different. There was a new king and queen, and

09:56.240 --> 09:58.720
I wasn't important in France anymore,

09:59.440 --> 10:06.160
but I was still queen of Scots. So I came

10:06.160 --> 10:07.560
back to Scotland.

10:10.320 --> 10:14.680
When I arrived in Scotland, I was a young girl

10:14.680 --> 10:20.400
of 18. My mother was dead, and there was no

10:20.400 --> 10:20.740
one

10:20.740 --> 10:26.660
there to meet me. I walked off the ship, and

10:26.660 --> 10:29.340
I slept in a little house near the sea.

10:32.040 --> 10:38.240
Next day, the Scots' lords came from Edinburgh. They were

10:38.240 --> 10:39.300
pleased to see me,

10:39.900 --> 10:45.560
and for a week everyone was happy. People smiled at

10:45.560 --> 10:47.580
me and sang in the streets.

10:47.580 --> 10:56.120
I think everyone liked me. Then, that Sunday, I went

10:56.120 --> 10:56.500
to church.

10:58.920 --> 11:06.300
James, my son, you are a Protestant, and I am

11:06.300 --> 11:06.740
a Catholic.

11:08.700 --> 11:13.580
You are a good man, and you love God, but

11:13.580 --> 11:16.760
your church and my church are enemies.

11:18.120 --> 11:21.800
I was born a Catholic, and I am going to

11:21.800 --> 11:28.440
die a Catholic. I love God, too. I hope you

11:28.440 --> 11:28.680
understand

11:28.680 --> 11:35.580
that. I'm not going to change now. That Sunday, people

11:35.580 --> 11:37.560
shouted angrily in the streets.

11:38.540 --> 11:44.320
Your Majesty, said the Scots' lords. Scotland is a Protestant

11:44.320 --> 11:47.240
country. You can't go to a Catholic

11:47.240 --> 11:54.900
church here. The Scottish people don't like Catholics. I'm sorry,

11:55.300 --> 11:59.400
my lords, I said, but I am your queen.

12:00.120 --> 12:04.960
No one tells me what to do. I don't hate

12:04.960 --> 12:08.620
Protestants, and I'm not going to kill them.

12:09.680 --> 12:13.820
The people can go to their Protestant churches and pray

12:13.820 --> 12:17.760
to God there, but I'm going to pray

12:17.760 --> 12:25.440
with Catholics in my church. People were angry because of

12:25.440 --> 12:28.660
that. A man called John

12:28.660 --> 12:34.120
Knox came to see me. He was a famous Protestant

12:34.120 --> 12:37.740
churchman, but I didn't like him.

12:38.940 --> 12:44.820
He was a big, angry man with black clothes. He

12:44.820 --> 12:49.080
hated the Catholic church and wanted all

12:49.080 --> 12:56.420
Catholics to leave Scotland. To him, the Protestant church was

12:56.420 --> 12:57.440
the only true

12:57.440 --> 13:04.040
church of God. He said, Your Majesty, you're a young

13:04.040 --> 13:06.000
woman like my daughter.

13:06.960 --> 13:12.100
Women can understand difficult things like God or the church.

13:13.100 --> 13:15.020
Find a good, Protestant

13:15.020 --> 13:21.960
husband girl. Let him rule this country for you. I

13:21.960 --> 13:24.060
was very angry with this man, Knox.

13:25.160 --> 13:30.480
I was a queen, but I was only 18. He

13:30.480 --> 13:36.200
didn't talk quietly. He shouted at me. I cried because

13:36.200 --> 13:41.480
of his angry words. I could not understand him. He

13:41.480 --> 13:44.940
talked so much, and he knew so many books.

13:46.400 --> 13:48.580
But I did not go to his church.

13:51.400 --> 13:57.160
He was right about one thing. Perhaps I could rule

13:57.160 --> 14:01.280
Scotland without a man, but I could not

14:01.280 --> 14:06.420
have a child without one. And every queen needs a

14:06.420 --> 14:09.520
son or daughter to come after her.

14:11.280 --> 14:14.180
So I began to look for a husband.

14:33.340 --> 14:34.640
Chapter 3

14:35.760 --> 14:37.740
Darnley and Riccio

14:39.360 --> 14:43.120
At first, I wanted to marry the son of the

14:43.120 --> 14:45.460
king of Spain, Don Carlos.

14:47.320 --> 14:51.780
But he was a Catholic, of course, and my Scots

14:51.780 --> 14:53.900
lords did not like that.

14:56.030 --> 15:00.620
It was difficult for me, James. I wanted to please

15:00.620 --> 15:01.140
myself.

15:02.180 --> 15:05.860
I wanted to please my friends and family in France,

15:07.180 --> 15:09.320
and to please my people too.

15:10.260 --> 15:13.620
And then there was the queen of England.

15:16.060 --> 15:20.240
At first, I wanted very much to be friends with

15:20.240 --> 15:20.420
Elizabeth.

15:21.820 --> 15:26.480
We wrote many letters and talked about a meeting, a

15:26.480 --> 15:29.380
meeting between two sister queens.

15:31.460 --> 15:34.460
Elizabeth wrote to me at this time.

15:35.680 --> 15:42.080
Are two countries need to be friends? You need a

15:42.080 --> 15:42.440
husband.

15:43.480 --> 15:49.740
I need a friend. Why not marry my friend Robert

15:49.740 --> 15:52.340
Dudley, the Earl of Leicester?

15:53.600 --> 15:58.620
He is a tall, strong man. I think he could

15:58.620 --> 16:01.080
be a good husband for you.

16:02.820 --> 16:06.740
I was very angry about this letter.

16:08.390 --> 16:12.620
There were a lot of stories about Elizabeth and Robert

16:12.620 --> 16:13.000
Dudley.

16:14.690 --> 16:21.020
They were good friends. He often danced and sang and

16:21.020 --> 16:21.980
talked with her.

16:23.040 --> 16:28.580
Sometimes, people said, he stayed in her room all night.

16:30.340 --> 16:36.500
Dudley had a wife, but one day, she died very

16:36.500 --> 16:36.920
suddenly.

16:38.420 --> 16:44.220
It was an accident. She fell down the stairs, they

16:44.220 --> 16:44.500
say.

16:46.280 --> 16:52.100
But then, perhaps she was unhappy because of her husband

16:52.100 --> 16:53.180
and Elizabeth.

16:53.820 --> 16:58.940
And she writes to me about a man like this,

16:59.760 --> 17:00.280
I thought.

17:01.960 --> 17:05.760
She wants him to marry me because he is her

17:05.760 --> 17:08.760
friend, her lover, perhaps.

17:09.560 --> 17:13.420
She wants her lover to be king of Scotland.

17:15.760 --> 17:19.000
I found a better man than Dudley, James.

17:20.180 --> 17:27.400
I found Henry Dudley, your father. He was 19 years

17:27.400 --> 17:30.100
old, and I was 23.

17:31.780 --> 17:36.880
He was a tall man with a beautiful face and

17:36.880 --> 17:38.320
big green eyes.

17:39.440 --> 17:44.860
He talked and sang well, and I liked dancing with

17:44.860 --> 17:45.080
him.

17:45.880 --> 17:51.740
He often wore expensive black clothes, and he laughed a

17:51.740 --> 17:53.300
lot when he was with me.

17:54.560 --> 17:59.420
He was very young and friendly, and I felt happy

17:59.420 --> 18:00.760
when I was with him.

18:01.700 --> 18:07.080
I liked him very much, and I thought he loved

18:07.080 --> 18:07.700
me too.

18:09.540 --> 18:14.140
He was an important man too. We were cousins.

18:15.480 --> 18:20.980
His grandfather was king of Scots, and his great grandfather

18:20.980 --> 18:24.000
was Henry VII of England.

18:26.240 --> 18:34.380
In July 1565, I married him. Elizabeth was very angry,

18:34.860 --> 18:36.880
and so were a lot of the

18:36.880 --> 18:44.340
Scots lords. My half-brother, the Earl of Moray, tried

18:44.340 --> 18:45.440
to stop the marriage.

18:46.480 --> 18:51.020
I had to fight him, and he ran south to

18:51.020 --> 18:54.680
England. But I was happy.

18:55.860 --> 19:01.860
Your father and I laughed every day. He was now

19:01.860 --> 19:03.880
Henry, king of Scots.

19:07.300 --> 19:11.900
After one or two weeks, the laughter stopped.

19:13.540 --> 19:17.500
A king has a lot of work, James. You know

19:17.500 --> 19:17.780
that.

19:19.040 --> 19:23.440
He has to read hundreds of letters, talk to people,

19:23.880 --> 19:26.940
and think about a lot of important things.

19:28.580 --> 19:35.120
I did those things every day. But now, I thought,

19:35.560 --> 19:37.620
I had a man to help me.

19:39.540 --> 19:44.220
My Lord Henry, I said, would you like to read

19:44.220 --> 19:45.580
all the letters with me?

19:46.320 --> 19:49.700
You can sit next to me, and you can work

19:49.700 --> 19:50.980
with me every day.

19:52.800 --> 19:54.740
Your father looked unhappy.

19:56.700 --> 20:02.940
I'm not interested in work like that, he said. I

20:02.940 --> 20:03.900
don't understand it.

20:05.480 --> 20:10.360
Of course not, I said. You're a young man, my

20:10.360 --> 20:13.100
love. But I can teach you.

20:15.380 --> 20:19.000
For one or two days, he sat down with me,

20:19.620 --> 20:21.140
and I tried to teach him.

20:22.240 --> 20:27.680
But it was true. He was not interested in the

20:27.680 --> 20:31.460
work, and he did not try to understand it.

20:33.260 --> 20:38.380
You do it, Mary. He said, I'm going out with

20:38.380 --> 20:42.440
my friends. We're going to ride, and drink,

20:43.160 --> 20:50.720
and swim. So, I did all the work. At night,

20:51.100 --> 20:54.320
too, he often went out with his friends in the

20:54.320 --> 20:54.600
town.

20:55.580 --> 21:01.160
They drank a lot, and laughed and sang, and there

21:01.160 --> 21:01.940
were often fights.

21:03.500 --> 21:08.000
But no one said anything, because he was the king,

21:08.780 --> 21:09.880
my husband.

21:11.440 --> 21:18.660
What could people say? They were unhappy, but they were

21:18.660 --> 21:19.520
afraid of him.

21:21.180 --> 21:25.600
Some of them went to England, to the Earl of

21:25.600 --> 21:26.020
Moray.

21:28.240 --> 21:33.000
At this time, I was often very tired, because I

21:33.000 --> 21:33.440
was pregnant.

21:34.320 --> 21:39.400
You, my son James, were alive inside me.

21:41.260 --> 21:45.540
But I did all the work of a queen, and

21:45.540 --> 21:47.120
I needed friends, too.

21:49.020 --> 21:54.980
One of these friends was a young Italian, David Ricchio.

21:57.680 --> 22:02.740
Ricchio was a little man, and he was not tall,

22:03.640 --> 22:06.020
or beautiful, or strong.

22:08.000 --> 22:13.120
But he was a very clever, interesting man. He wrote

22:13.120 --> 22:16.980
many of my letters for me, and helped me.

22:16.980 --> 22:23.400
He sang well, too, and I sometimes sang with him

22:23.400 --> 22:24.660
in the evenings.

22:27.090 --> 22:33.040
I liked him very much, and at first, your father

22:33.040 --> 22:34.160
liked him, too.

22:35.800 --> 22:40.260
But then, Moray's friends began to talk about me and

22:40.260 --> 22:40.720
Ricchio.

22:42.000 --> 22:46.160
David Ricchio is in the Queen's rooms every night.

22:47.040 --> 22:51.320
They said to your father, she laughs, and sings, and

22:51.320 --> 22:52.480
dances with him.

22:53.080 --> 22:56.760
My lord, it is not right. He is not a

22:56.760 --> 22:59.320
Scotsman, and he is not her husband.

23:00.120 --> 23:01.780
He is always with her.

23:03.800 --> 23:06.740
Perhaps they said other things, too.

23:07.680 --> 23:08.880
I don't know.

23:10.720 --> 23:13.380
A lot of Scots lords listened to them.

23:15.180 --> 23:20.500
But I tell you, James, before God, I did nothing

23:20.500 --> 23:21.200
wrong.

23:22.740 --> 23:25.720
David Ricchio was a good man.

23:27.440 --> 23:31.940
He worked hard, and he helped me. So, of course,

23:32.300 --> 23:33.000
I liked him.

23:33.900 --> 23:38.740
Your father did not work. He went out to the

23:38.740 --> 23:42.400
town every night with his friends and drank.

23:43.900 --> 23:47.640
And then, one night, your father came home.

24:08.560 --> 24:09.860
Chapter 4

24:10.940 --> 24:13.280
The Death of David Ricchio

24:15.260 --> 24:19.540
It was a Saturday evening in March 1566.

24:20.820 --> 24:23.620
I was in Edinburgh with some friends.

24:24.820 --> 24:29.760
David Ricchio was there, with six or seven other people.

24:31.120 --> 24:34.540
We were in a small room, but there was a

24:34.540 --> 24:37.800
good dinner on the table, and we were happy.

24:39.340 --> 24:45.000
It was dark outside, but inside it was warm and

24:45.000 --> 24:45.480
friendly.

24:47.300 --> 24:50.620
Suddenly, a door opened behind me.

24:52.320 --> 24:56.580
In the door was Henry Darnley, my husband.

24:56.580 --> 25:00.320
I stood up and smiled.

25:01.860 --> 25:03.500
Good evening, my lord.

25:04.500 --> 25:06.760
I said, please come in.

25:07.840 --> 25:09.600
Would you like something to eat?

25:10.900 --> 25:12.240
No, thank you.

25:13.160 --> 25:18.440
He said, I'm not hungry, but I want to sit

25:18.440 --> 25:19.640
next to you, wife.

25:21.100 --> 25:23.540
Please tell that man to move.

25:26.580 --> 25:29.100
A man got out of the chair next to me,

25:29.760 --> 25:31.800
and Darnley sat beside me.

25:33.200 --> 25:38.080
Then he put his arms around me. I did not

25:38.080 --> 25:38.680
like it.

25:39.860 --> 25:44.040
His face was hot, and his eyes looked unhappy.

25:45.440 --> 25:49.760
But I smiled and said, I'm happy to see you,

25:50.000 --> 25:50.500
my lord.

25:51.820 --> 25:53.620
Are you, Mary?

25:54.360 --> 25:55.360
He laughed.

25:56.360 --> 25:57.460
Are you really?

25:58.560 --> 26:01.100
Yes, of course, my lord.

26:02.060 --> 26:08.040
But then the second door opened, and his friend, Lord

26:08.040 --> 26:09.160
Ruth and stood there.

26:10.300 --> 26:12.360
He had a knife in his hand.

26:13.380 --> 26:17.820
His face was red, and he looked very angry.

26:19.840 --> 26:22.360
At first, no one moved.

26:24.060 --> 26:30.320
Then Ruth and said, your majesty, send David Ricchio out

26:30.320 --> 26:31.600
of this room now.

26:32.420 --> 26:33.260
I want him.

26:35.100 --> 26:36.740
I looked at Ricchio.

26:37.620 --> 26:38.740
He was afraid.

26:40.500 --> 26:41.220
Why?

26:42.100 --> 26:45.000
I said, why do you want him?

26:45.900 --> 26:49.260
He is a bad, wicked man.

26:50.260 --> 26:52.800
Ruth and said, send him out.

26:55.000 --> 26:59.060
No, I said, you want to kill him.

27:00.040 --> 27:05.260
David Ricchio is my friend. He stays here, with me.

27:06.500 --> 27:08.620
He goes out, woman.

27:09.680 --> 27:14.680
Lord Ruth and said, King Henry, hold your wife, please.

27:16.400 --> 27:20.760
I stood up, but darnly held my arms, and I

27:20.760 --> 27:21.580
could not move.

27:23.500 --> 27:27.340
David Ricchio ran behind me, and held my dress.

27:28.480 --> 27:32.340
My friends in the room stood up, too, and moved

27:32.340 --> 27:34.300
towards Ruth and angrily.

27:35.660 --> 27:38.600
But he had a knife in his hand.

27:39.980 --> 27:44.800
Get back, he said, angrily, don't touch me.

27:46.000 --> 27:49.340
Then five men with knives ran into the little room,

27:49.960 --> 27:51.440
and there was a fight.

27:53.480 --> 27:58.220
One man held a knife in my face, and another

27:58.220 --> 28:01.520
man hit David Ricchio behind me.

28:02.500 --> 28:05.080
Then they pulled him out of the room.

28:05.840 --> 28:08.080
Help me, he screamed.

28:09.080 --> 28:11.060
Help me, my queen, please.

28:11.740 --> 28:14.020
They're going to kill me, don't...

28:14.020 --> 28:21.000
I couldn't help him, because darnly had me in his

28:21.000 --> 28:21.280
arms.

28:22.760 --> 28:25.400
But I could hear David Ricchio's screams.

28:26.800 --> 28:28.740
I think he fell down the stairs,

28:28.740 --> 28:32.460
and he screamed for two or three minutes.

28:34.260 --> 28:36.180
Then it was quiet.

28:38.060 --> 28:39.820
What are you doing?

28:40.880 --> 28:42.420
I asked darnly angrily.

28:43.780 --> 28:45.520
Ricchio is a good man.

28:46.460 --> 28:48.000
Why are you doing this?

28:49.480 --> 28:50.500
Darnly laughed.

28:51.860 --> 28:54.900
You are my wife, Mary.

28:55.940 --> 28:57.660
Not David Ricchio's.

28:58.740 --> 29:02.680
He said, so why are you with him every evening?

29:03.440 --> 29:05.000
You never talk to me.

29:06.740 --> 29:10.340
I don't talk to you, because you are never here.

29:11.220 --> 29:14.820
I said, you are always drinking with your friends.

29:15.640 --> 29:16.940
You aren't a king.

29:17.880 --> 29:19.440
You're a stupid boy.

29:21.000 --> 29:22.400
He laughed again.

29:23.580 --> 29:25.260
It was not a nice laugh.

29:27.440 --> 29:34.000
Well, he said, perhaps I am a boy, but that

29:34.000 --> 29:36.800
is better than David Ricchio now.

29:37.880 --> 29:40.140
Do you want to go and see him?

29:42.240 --> 29:46.060
I did see him, five minutes after that.

29:47.600 --> 29:52.680
He was very dead, and there was blood all over

29:52.680 --> 29:53.100
the floor.

29:55.220 --> 29:57.220
Poor David Ricchio.

30:00.240 --> 30:03.360
He sings to God now, not me.

30:06.880 --> 30:10.000
I looked at Henry Darnly, my husband.

30:11.240 --> 30:13.840
He had a stupid smile on his face,

30:15.740 --> 30:17.880
but I think he was afraid of me.

30:20.040 --> 30:22.340
I looked at him a long time.

30:23.100 --> 30:24.900
And the smile went away.

30:27.480 --> 30:30.080
Remember this night, husband.

30:31.360 --> 30:35.020
I said to him, remember it well.

30:36.900 --> 30:41.840
Think about it when you look into my eyes, and

30:41.840 --> 30:43.460
before you go to sleep.

30:45.420 --> 30:51.720
David Ricchio was my friend, and you killed him in

30:51.720 --> 30:52.560
front of me.

30:53.760 --> 30:58.320
I'm never going to forget that, Henry Darnly.

30:59.560 --> 31:00.120
Never.

31:03.760 --> 31:05.160
Never.

31:18.920 --> 31:20.320
Chapter 5

31:21.240 --> 31:23.080
My son is born.

31:26.140 --> 31:29.880
Next morning, Darnly came to see me.

31:31.480 --> 31:32.360
He was afraid.

31:34.640 --> 31:36.320
What's the matter, husband?

31:37.420 --> 31:40.520
I said, why are you crying?

31:43.220 --> 31:45.400
Mary, Mary.

31:46.560 --> 31:50.300
He said, I'm sorry, I was wrong.

31:51.230 --> 31:55.140
I helped those men to kill Ricchio, and now the

31:55.140 --> 31:57.320
Earl of Moray is back here with them.

31:58.080 --> 31:59.080
He hates me.

31:59.920 --> 32:03.480
I'm afraid they're going to kill me, and you too.

32:04.560 --> 32:06.280
Think of our child, Mary.

32:07.340 --> 32:08.320
Here inside you.

32:11.060 --> 32:13.140
He took me in his arms again.

32:14.460 --> 32:16.200
I was very angry.

32:17.940 --> 32:22.780
I am sorry, James, that this man was your father.

32:23.820 --> 32:27.520
He was a stupid boy, not a man.

32:29.000 --> 32:35.220
He was tall, and strong, and beautiful, but he could

32:35.220 --> 32:38.740
never think like a man, or a king.

32:40.640 --> 32:44.720
I said, you know these men, Henry.

32:45.800 --> 32:47.140
What do they want?

32:50.420 --> 32:53.400
They want our child, Mary.

32:54.320 --> 32:55.660
They don't want us.

32:56.560 --> 32:58.760
They're going to put you in prison.

32:59.980 --> 33:01.860
They don't want you to be queen.

33:03.110 --> 33:06.740
They want your child to be king or queen.

33:08.000 --> 33:12.360
I don't know what they want to do with me.

33:14.720 --> 33:20.060
Perhaps they want you to be king too, without me,

33:20.880 --> 33:22.460
I said quietly.

33:24.760 --> 33:29.160
Then you can do what they say, like a little

33:29.160 --> 33:29.580
boy.

33:31.520 --> 33:35.240
Perhaps, Mary, they said that yesterday.

33:36.240 --> 33:39.960
But now that Moray's here, I don't know.

33:40.200 --> 33:40.580
I'm afraid.

33:41.300 --> 33:42.500
Please help me.

33:42.500 --> 33:45.800
He began to cry again.

33:46.820 --> 33:47.760
What can we do?

33:49.700 --> 33:52.700
We can run away, I said.

33:54.060 --> 33:58.840
We can leave Edinburgh quickly and quietly, before Ruthbun and

33:58.840 --> 33:59.780
his men stop us.

34:00.940 --> 34:02.560
Be quiet for a minute.

34:03.760 --> 34:04.800
I want to think.

34:06.640 --> 34:10.160
I walked up and down for two or three minutes.

34:11.100 --> 34:12.400
Then I said,

34:14.600 --> 34:17.600
Henry, go back to these men.

34:18.480 --> 34:19.380
Tell them?

34:20.440 --> 34:22.640
No, Mary, please.

34:23.680 --> 34:24.580
I can't.

34:24.960 --> 34:26.400
I'm afraid of them.

34:28.000 --> 34:32.320
Listen to me, Henry, and try to be a man.

34:33.320 --> 34:37.980
Go and tell them I'm ill, because of the child.

34:38.860 --> 34:40.940
Say I'm not angry with them.

34:41.800 --> 34:44.520
Tell them anything, lie to them.

34:45.580 --> 34:52.180
Then tonight, bring some men and horses here, behind the

34:52.180 --> 34:52.500
castle.

34:55.660 --> 34:58.140
He went and did it.

34:59.640 --> 35:03.500
All day, I waited in my rooms and listened.

35:05.640 --> 35:08.120
Then, at one o'clock in the morning,

35:09.400 --> 35:14.300
Darnley and I went quietly down the stairs, behind the

35:14.300 --> 35:14.540
castle.

35:16.760 --> 35:21.100
Some of my friends were there, with horses for us.

35:22.560 --> 35:25.820
Quickly, we rode away into the night.

35:27.480 --> 35:29.740
That was a very bad night.

35:30.320 --> 35:33.560
It was dark and cold.

35:34.860 --> 35:38.820
I was ill, and Darnley was afraid.

35:40.680 --> 35:41.920
Come on.

35:43.240 --> 35:46.300
He said, ride faster, woman.

35:47.180 --> 35:48.000
You're too slow.

35:49.320 --> 35:54.480
But I was pregnant, and it was cold and dark.

35:55.720 --> 35:59.060
We rode for five hours in the rain.

36:00.360 --> 36:02.340
I can't, Henry.

36:03.380 --> 36:05.580
I said, I'm ill.

36:06.680 --> 36:07.900
Think of the baby.

36:08.780 --> 36:10.620
I don't want it to die.

36:12.720 --> 36:13.520
Why not?

36:14.560 --> 36:18.200
He said, we can always make another one.

36:19.960 --> 36:23.160
I'm sorry, but it is true.

36:23.960 --> 36:26.840
Your father said things like that, James.

36:29.740 --> 36:33.720
Then he rode away in front of me, into the

36:33.720 --> 36:34.000
dark.

36:36.220 --> 36:41.840
I rode slowly behind, with my good woman, Bess Co.

36:45.000 --> 36:48.620
In the morning, we arrived at Dunbar Castle.

36:50.380 --> 36:54.760
Darnley slept, and I wrote letters to my friends.

36:56.440 --> 37:00.220
Next day, Lord Bothwell came to help me.

37:01.380 --> 37:02.600
I liked him.

37:03.520 --> 37:06.240
He was a good, strong man.

37:08.200 --> 37:12.280
Soon, I had an army of 8,000 men.

37:14.260 --> 37:18.000
Bothwell and I rode back to Edinburgh with the army.

37:19.720 --> 37:24.080
Lord Ruth then died, and some of his friends ran

37:24.080 --> 37:24.380
away,

37:25.640 --> 37:27.780
but the Earl of Moray stayed.

37:30.300 --> 37:35.940
All that summer, I ruled the country and waited for

37:35.940 --> 37:36.340
the baby.

37:37.900 --> 37:41.140
My husband stayed outside my rooms.

37:42.380 --> 37:44.560
I did not want to see him.

37:45.520 --> 37:46.580
No one did.

37:47.480 --> 37:51.460
Perhaps he drank with his friends, I don't know.

37:53.880 --> 37:58.940
And then, on the 19th of June, in a small

37:58.940 --> 38:01.120
room in Edinburgh Castle,

38:02.380 --> 38:04.060
my baby was born.

38:05.700 --> 38:11.040
It took a long time, but at last you were

38:11.040 --> 38:11.860
in my arms.

38:14.040 --> 38:19.440
James, my son, I asked your father to come in.

38:20.660 --> 38:26.600
My Lord Henry, I said, this is our baby.

38:28.000 --> 38:29.520
Look at him, my Lord.

38:30.340 --> 38:32.000
Take him in your arms.

38:33.140 --> 38:34.840
He is your son.

38:35.900 --> 38:37.380
Isn't he beautiful?

38:39.860 --> 38:43.240
But your father did not love me, James.

38:44.820 --> 38:50.060
Very often, after you were born, he slept with other

38:50.060 --> 38:50.340
women.

38:51.840 --> 38:56.200
I know that because he talked to everyone about it.

38:57.360 --> 39:00.840
I think he wanted people to know.

39:02.720 --> 39:08.180
And, I am sorry, but I do not think he

39:08.180 --> 39:09.260
loved you, James.

39:11.310 --> 39:15.420
When I took you to church and gave you your

39:15.420 --> 39:17.960
name, he did not come.

39:19.260 --> 39:20.540
He wasn't interested.

39:22.610 --> 39:27.140
But because of him, David Riccio was dead.

39:27.140 --> 39:31.040
I could never forget that.

39:32.320 --> 39:33.020
Never.

39:50.260 --> 39:53.060
Chapter 6

39:54.560 --> 39:55.280
Kirkerfield

39:57.880 --> 40:02.080
I had a new man to help me now, the

40:02.080 --> 40:06.880
Earl of Bothewell, a strong clever man.

40:08.100 --> 40:09.640
He was older than me.

40:10.540 --> 40:13.000
He was not a boy like Darnley.

40:13.840 --> 40:17.340
He worked hard, and he could think.

40:17.340 --> 40:22.140
He was a good fighter, and he was not afraid

40:22.140 --> 40:23.360
of other men.

40:24.620 --> 40:29.060
Perhaps you are like him, James, my son.

40:31.380 --> 40:36.500
In January, your father, Darnley, was ill in Glasgow.

40:38.480 --> 40:42.220
I went to see him, and took him back to

40:42.220 --> 40:42.420
Edinburgh.

40:43.060 --> 40:47.760
He was unhappy, and afraid of people.

40:49.000 --> 40:51.960
He saw enemies behind every door.

40:53.280 --> 40:55.060
Poor, stupid boy.

40:56.260 --> 40:58.640
He said he loved me again.

40:59.640 --> 41:04.560
I was angry, but I felt sorry for him too.

41:05.960 --> 41:07.620
He was very ill.

41:08.920 --> 41:11.320
It's not far now, Henry.

41:11.320 --> 41:15.640
I said, you can sleep in the castle.

41:17.290 --> 41:19.140
No, not there.

41:19.780 --> 41:21.880
Please, Mary, he said.

41:22.620 --> 41:25.000
I don't want to go into the castle.

41:25.820 --> 41:27.320
I'm afraid of it.

41:28.830 --> 41:31.120
But where do you want to go?

41:32.040 --> 41:32.540
I asked.

41:34.320 --> 41:39.560
Find me a little house outside the town, and stay

41:39.560 --> 41:40.340
with me there.

41:41.320 --> 41:44.320
He said, we can be happy there.

41:45.820 --> 41:51.320
So I found him a small house called Kirkafield, outside

41:51.320 --> 41:51.880
Edinburgh.

41:53.800 --> 42:00.400
He stayed there in a room upstairs, and sometimes I

42:00.400 --> 42:02.040
slept in a room downstairs.

42:03.860 --> 42:09.900
Darnley was often afraid, and I visited him every day.

42:11.240 --> 42:13.920
Slowly, he got better.

42:16.660 --> 42:20.460
On Sunday the 9th of February, there was a big

42:20.460 --> 42:21.780
wedding in Edinburgh.

42:23.800 --> 42:28.660
After the wedding, Bothwell and I walked out to Kirkafield

42:28.660 --> 42:31.680
to see Darnley and talk to him.

42:32.980 --> 42:37.620
Everyone sang and laughed, and was very happy.

42:39.620 --> 42:42.460
At 10 o'clock, I was tired.

42:44.400 --> 42:46.160
Good night, my lords.

42:47.300 --> 42:50.340
I said, I'm going downstairs to bed.

42:51.900 --> 42:54.780
Lord Bothwell put his hand on my arm.

42:56.040 --> 43:01.580
Your majesty, he said, you can't sleep here now.

43:02.680 --> 43:03.760
Don't you remember?

43:04.560 --> 43:08.200
People are dancing and singing in town tonight.

43:09.180 --> 43:10.840
Everyone wants you to go.

43:12.600 --> 43:15.480
Oh, yes, I forgot.

43:16.580 --> 43:20.220
I said, of course, people want to see me there.

43:21.500 --> 43:23.800
So, good night, Henry.

43:24.600 --> 43:25.360
Sleep well.

43:27.140 --> 43:29.280
Darnley was very unhappy.

43:31.100 --> 43:37.080
Please, Mary, my love, don't go, he said, don't leave

43:37.080 --> 43:37.740
me here.

43:40.780 --> 43:42.760
But I did not love him now.

43:44.020 --> 43:46.780
I remembered the night when Riccio died.

43:47.840 --> 43:51.920
So I smiled and said, good night, Henry.

43:52.920 --> 43:54.200
Be a man now.

43:55.700 --> 43:57.680
Don't be afraid of the dark.

44:01.020 --> 44:03.680
Then I went downstairs with Lord Bothwell.

44:05.000 --> 44:08.400
Outside the house, we met one of Bothwell's men.

44:10.100 --> 44:15.240
He looked afraid, and there was something black on his

44:15.240 --> 44:16.500
face and hands.

44:18.200 --> 44:20.560
Jesus, man, how dirty you are.

44:21.440 --> 44:24.660
I said, don't come near me with those hands.

44:26.060 --> 44:27.660
Normal lady, I said, don't come near me with those

44:27.660 --> 44:27.660
hands.

44:27.680 --> 44:28.560
Of course not.

44:29.720 --> 44:34.780
He said, he looked at Bothwell for a minute and

44:34.780 --> 44:36.120
then ran away quickly.

44:37.300 --> 44:42.080
I laughed, got on my horse and forgot about it.

44:43.610 --> 44:49.280
I tell you before God, James, I did not kill

44:49.280 --> 44:50.160
your father.

44:50.860 --> 44:52.320
It was not me.

44:53.160 --> 44:56.480
I knew nothing about it, nothing.

44:58.400 --> 45:03.300
I sang and danced in town and then went to

45:03.300 --> 45:05.180
bed in Edinburgh Castle.

45:06.780 --> 45:11.160
Then, at two o'clock in the morning, there was

45:11.160 --> 45:15.620
a sudden noise, a very big bang.

45:17.040 --> 45:20.120
Everybody heard it all through the town.

45:21.040 --> 45:25.100
My God, I said, what's that?

45:27.000 --> 45:29.260
Everyone ran out of their rooms.

45:30.660 --> 45:32.120
Lord Bothwell was downstairs.

45:34.020 --> 45:36.360
Don't be afraid, ladies.

45:37.460 --> 45:40.120
He said, my men are outside.

45:41.360 --> 45:43.080
They're going to see what it is.

45:45.660 --> 45:48.980
After an hour, he came to see me.

45:50.280 --> 45:54.020
Please, sit down, my lady, he said.

45:55.100 --> 45:57.260
I have some unhappy news.

45:59.400 --> 46:00.340
Yes, my lord.

46:01.440 --> 46:02.200
What is it?

46:03.400 --> 46:06.600
It's your husband, Lord Darnley.

46:07.860 --> 46:09.040
He is dead.

46:11.200 --> 46:12.880
But how?

46:13.640 --> 46:14.940
How did he die?

46:16.300 --> 46:17.320
Who killed him?

46:19.240 --> 46:20.760
I don't know, my lady.

46:21.360 --> 46:24.800
That bang, that was his house.

46:26.140 --> 46:29.460
Kerkerfield, it's not there anymore.

46:31.420 --> 46:32.000
What?

46:33.040 --> 46:34.920
And Darnley was inside?

46:36.880 --> 46:40.680
Well, no, my lady.

46:42.280 --> 46:43.440
Bothwell said slowly.

46:45.340 --> 46:50.480
My men found him in the garden, not in the

46:50.480 --> 46:50.740
house.

46:52.120 --> 46:55.140
He is wearing only night clothes.

46:56.540 --> 46:58.880
And there is no blood on him.

47:00.160 --> 47:01.360
But he is dead.

47:02.640 --> 47:03.740
I am sorry.

47:04.960 --> 47:06.240
Take me out there.

47:07.100 --> 47:08.320
I want to see him.

47:09.280 --> 47:09.380
Now.

47:10.680 --> 47:12.180
Yes, my lady.

47:13.440 --> 47:16.600
I went out to Kerkerfield in the early morning.

47:18.460 --> 47:19.980
There was no house now.

47:21.040 --> 47:27.120
No walls, no doors, no windows, nothing.

47:28.500 --> 47:32.560
And there in the garden, a long way from the

47:32.560 --> 47:32.860
house,

47:33.940 --> 47:37.960
was that poor, dead boy, my husband.

47:40.920 --> 47:42.240
I did not love him.

47:43.440 --> 47:45.000
But I cried then.

47:46.660 --> 47:48.500
He was your father, James.

47:49.500 --> 47:51.920
And I did not kill him.

47:53.460 --> 47:55.580
I don't know who killed him.

47:57.160 --> 48:00.180
But he had many enemies in Scotland.

48:03.360 --> 48:04.700
I was very afraid.

48:05.520 --> 48:07.840
I too had enemies.

48:08.640 --> 48:10.540
And I often slept there.

48:10.540 --> 48:15.680
Perhaps someone wanted to kill me too.

48:34.580 --> 48:35.920
Chapter 7.

48:37.060 --> 48:37.760
Bothwell.

48:40.540 --> 48:43.180
Soon everyone in Europe heard the news.

48:44.640 --> 48:47.680
The Queen of France and the Queen of England

48:48.050 --> 48:49.980
wrote angry letters to me.

48:51.460 --> 48:53.120
Who killed the king?

48:54.360 --> 48:54.880
They asked.

48:56.380 --> 48:59.300
I was very unhappy at this time, James.

49:00.620 --> 49:04.420
We looked for the killers, but we could not find

49:04.420 --> 49:04.680
them.

49:05.960 --> 49:07.940
Please believe me, James.

49:07.940 --> 49:11.980
The Scots' lords are difficult men.

49:13.260 --> 49:16.320
Some were friends, some were enemies.

49:17.820 --> 49:19.800
But they changed all the time.

49:22.460 --> 49:24.560
Many people in Scotland said,

49:25.380 --> 49:27.900
Bothwell killed Lord Darnley.

49:29.180 --> 49:33.720
I heard them outside the castle and in the town.

49:35.120 --> 49:36.700
But I never believed it.

49:37.940 --> 49:42.640
People in Edinburgh sold horrible stories and pictures of Bothwell,

49:43.140 --> 49:46.380
the same day that Darnley died.

49:47.860 --> 49:49.560
It was too soon.

49:51.180 --> 49:56.000
Perhaps Darnley's killers wrote these stories about Bothwell

49:56.380 --> 49:58.780
before they killed Darnley.

50:00.960 --> 50:05.420
I don't think Lord Bothwell killed your father, James.

50:06.480 --> 50:10.400
He was a good friend to me in difficult times.

50:11.580 --> 50:15.980
He was a good, strong, clever man.

50:16.960 --> 50:18.120
And he worked hard.

50:18.980 --> 50:20.080
I liked that.

50:20.920 --> 50:24.020
A lot of women liked him, I think.

50:25.740 --> 50:30.180
Three times that spring, he asked me to marry him.

50:31.520 --> 50:35.400
He had a wife, and I could not marry again

50:35.400 --> 50:36.440
so soon.

50:37.760 --> 50:39.100
I asked him to wait.

50:41.220 --> 50:45.780
Then, on the 24th of April, I rode out of

50:45.780 --> 50:47.060
Edinburgh to the north.

50:48.160 --> 50:50.920
I had five or six friends with me.

50:52.760 --> 50:57.880
Six miles outside the town, Lord Bothwell met us

50:59.000 --> 51:00.060
with an army.

51:01.880 --> 51:04.460
Why are you here, my Lord?

51:05.440 --> 51:05.820
I said.

51:07.080 --> 51:08.040
He smiled.

51:09.780 --> 51:13.640
Because I want to meet you, Mary, he said.

51:14.880 --> 51:18.060
I want you to come with me to my castle.

51:19.680 --> 51:23.700
He rode next to me, and his man rode between

51:23.700 --> 51:24.940
me and my friends.

51:25.580 --> 51:31.360
I was afraid, and a little excited too.

51:32.540 --> 51:37.200
But my Lord, you can't do this, I said.

51:38.480 --> 51:41.020
I don't want to come with you now.

51:42.900 --> 51:44.860
But I want you, Mary.

51:45.780 --> 51:49.120
He said, your friends can't stop me.

51:49.860 --> 51:53.180
I love you, and I want to marry you.

51:54.100 --> 51:55.620
What's wrong with that?

51:58.800 --> 51:59.900
I said nothing.

52:00.940 --> 52:02.380
What could I say?

52:04.020 --> 52:07.660
I liked him, and he had an army.

52:08.500 --> 52:10.620
I had only six friends.

52:12.360 --> 52:17.020
So, I rode with him to his castle in Dunbar,

52:18.760 --> 52:20.780
and stayed there two weeks.

52:21.680 --> 52:27.220
And then, he was a strong man, and I was

52:27.220 --> 52:27.960
only a woman.

52:29.240 --> 52:31.000
And I did like him, James.

52:32.200 --> 52:33.860
I liked him very much.

52:35.800 --> 52:37.780
After two weeks in Dunbar,

52:38.520 --> 52:40.700
Bothwell and I rode back to Edinburgh.

52:42.080 --> 52:46.100
His wife did not want him, and was happy to

52:46.100 --> 52:46.760
divorce him.

52:47.480 --> 52:52.040
So, on the 15th of May, 1567,

52:53.520 --> 52:54.980
I married him.

52:56.420 --> 52:58.640
He was a good man, James.

52:59.720 --> 53:01.860
A much better man than your father.

53:03.060 --> 53:06.420
I needed a strong man to help me rule the

53:06.420 --> 53:06.740
country.

53:08.840 --> 53:10.700
But, I was wrong.

53:11.760 --> 53:13.860
I understand that now.

53:15.320 --> 53:18.620
All the Scots lords were afraid of Bothwell,

53:19.220 --> 53:21.360
and many of them were his enemies.

53:23.620 --> 53:27.400
They had an army, and on the 15th of June,

53:27.800 --> 53:31.340
Bothwell and I rode out to fight them.

53:34.040 --> 53:36.180
We met them at Carbury Hill.

53:37.740 --> 53:41.740
It was a hot day, and the two big armies

53:41.740 --> 53:42.300
stood,

53:43.180 --> 53:45.540
and looked, and waited.

53:47.900 --> 53:50.540
Their army had a big flag,

53:51.460 --> 53:53.840
with a picture of your poor, dead father,

53:54.420 --> 53:55.520
darnly on it.

53:57.320 --> 54:00.240
Under the picture, there were the words,

54:01.140 --> 54:03.700
find my killers, oh God.

54:06.180 --> 54:10.020
Come on, my lord, I said to Bothwell,

54:10.900 --> 54:13.340
our army is better than theirs.

54:14.540 --> 54:15.620
Let's fight them.

54:18.420 --> 54:22.100
Bothwell rode up and down, and talked to his men.

54:23.540 --> 54:25.420
But they didn't want to fight.

54:26.780 --> 54:31.440
They talked, and looked at the flag, and waited.

54:33.640 --> 54:36.100
Then, some of them walked home.

54:37.420 --> 54:39.420
At five o'clock that evening,

54:40.260 --> 54:44.300
Lord Keir Khaldi rode from his army to talk to

54:44.300 --> 54:44.540
us.

54:46.100 --> 54:48.740
He said to me, my lady,

54:49.760 --> 54:52.020
leave your husband and come with us.

54:53.040 --> 54:55.080
We don't want men to die.

54:57.580 --> 55:01.500
And so, because our men didn't want to fight,

55:02.360 --> 55:03.700
I went with him.

55:06.100 --> 55:08.400
It was a very bad day for me.

55:09.620 --> 55:11.020
They took me back to Edinburgh,

55:11.940 --> 55:14.620
and people in the streets screamed at me.

55:15.280 --> 55:18.620
Kill the woman, she sleeps with her husband's killer.

55:19.560 --> 55:23.120
We want James to be king, kill her now.

55:25.440 --> 55:30.840
I was unhappy and afraid, and I was pregnant again.

55:33.520 --> 55:35.780
They took me to Lachlevan Castle,

55:37.340 --> 55:39.920
and put me in a room like a prison.

55:41.520 --> 55:44.240
There, I did not eat for two weeks.

55:45.860 --> 55:49.760
And Bothwell's children, there were two babies,

55:50.740 --> 55:51.840
were born dead.

55:53.580 --> 55:55.120
I nearly died, too.

55:56.260 --> 56:00.740
I was so angry and tired and ill.

56:02.800 --> 56:06.060
Then, one day after the babies died,

56:07.340 --> 56:09.100
Lord Lindsey gave me a letter.

56:10.640 --> 56:14.860
It said, I, Mary Queen of Scots,

56:16.100 --> 56:19.800
give the kingdom of Scotland to my son, James.

56:21.000 --> 56:26.780
From today, James is the new king of Scots.

56:28.980 --> 56:34.340
But, because he is a child, the Earl of Moray,

56:35.100 --> 56:39.440
my half-brother, can rule the country for him.

56:41.980 --> 56:45.960
Because I was afraid and tired and ill,

56:46.880 --> 56:51.320
I wrote my name on the letter, Mary.

56:52.580 --> 56:55.380
But, it is not important, James.

56:56.400 --> 56:58.120
It doesn't change anything.

56:59.080 --> 57:02.640
I am Queen of Scots, not you.

57:03.760 --> 57:05.860
That letter changes nothing.

57:07.960 --> 57:12.500
Bothwell went over the sea and died in a prison

57:12.500 --> 57:13.560
in Denmark.

57:15.960 --> 57:19.180
I was a prisoner in Lachleven for a year.

57:21.340 --> 57:24.660
A lot of people in Europe were angry about that.

57:26.400 --> 57:28.880
Queen Elizabeth wrote to the Earl of Moray,

57:29.860 --> 57:33.820
you cannot keep a queen in prison, she said.

57:34.780 --> 57:36.200
It is very wrong.

57:38.040 --> 57:42.500
I was pleased about that, but Moray didn't listen.

57:44.520 --> 57:49.060
Lord Douglas lived in the castle, and his young son,

57:49.300 --> 57:50.220
William, liked me.

57:52.140 --> 57:55.740
One day, there was a wedding in the castle.

57:57.300 --> 58:00.280
People sang and danced and drank.

58:02.240 --> 58:05.780
William Douglas gave me some old women's clothes.

58:05.780 --> 58:12.280
I put the clothes on and walked quietly out of

58:12.280 --> 58:13.280
the castle with him.

58:14.500 --> 58:18.760
He shut the castle door behind us to keep his

58:18.760 --> 58:20.000
father's friends in.

58:21.320 --> 58:26.860
Then, we got on some horses and rode away through

58:26.860 --> 58:27.280
the night.

58:28.960 --> 58:31.820
All my friends came back to me.

58:32.780 --> 58:34.760
Soon, I had a big army.

58:35.860 --> 58:39.100
Mary is our queen again, people said.

58:39.800 --> 58:41.320
Give her back her son.

58:42.940 --> 58:47.380
You were in Earl Moray's castle, James, so I came

58:47.380 --> 58:48.460
to fight him.

58:49.600 --> 58:55.400
I rode with my army to Langside, near Glasgow, and

58:55.400 --> 58:55.760
there.

58:57.840 --> 58:58.900
There, James.

59:00.520 --> 59:05.660
There, my son, I lost the fight.

59:07.700 --> 59:09.140
I am so sorry.

59:11.240 --> 59:17.160
I had many good, strong men in my army, but

59:17.160 --> 59:19.100
Earl Moray's men were stronger.

59:21.500 --> 59:25.740
Many of my men died, and some ran away.

59:27.020 --> 59:30.400
After the fight, I ran away too.

59:32.220 --> 59:36.060
I did not want to go to prison again, so

59:36.060 --> 59:39.300
I rode south to England.

59:40.700 --> 59:43.180
Queen Elizabeth wants to help me.

59:43.940 --> 59:50.260
I thought, she understands, she wrote to Moray, and she

59:50.260 --> 59:52.000
is a queen, like me.

59:53.240 --> 59:58.160
I can come back to Scotland with her army, kill

59:58.160 --> 01:00:01.860
Moray, and find my baby son, James.

01:00:03.100 --> 01:00:08.320
I am in England, but I am free. I can

01:00:08.320 --> 01:00:09.060
try again.

01:00:11.060 --> 01:00:15.140
I was wrong about that too. Very wrong.

01:00:33.820 --> 01:00:36.800
Chapter 8, England.

01:00:39.300 --> 01:00:44.480
Elizabeth didn't give me her army. She put me in

01:00:44.480 --> 01:00:44.760
prison.

01:00:46.480 --> 01:00:50.920
You know this, James. It is the story of your

01:00:50.920 --> 01:00:51.260
life.

01:00:52.000 --> 01:00:52.660
Not mine.

01:00:54.960 --> 01:00:58.520
I was 25 years old when I came to England,

01:00:59.500 --> 01:01:01.660
and I am 45 now.

01:01:03.410 --> 01:01:06.160
20 years in English prisons.

01:01:08.400 --> 01:01:11.460
Moray told lies about me.

01:01:11.460 --> 01:01:16.980
Mary and Bothwell killed Darnley, he said.

01:01:18.000 --> 01:01:24.160
Mary slept with Riccio and Bothwell, and killed her husband.

01:01:25.560 --> 01:01:31.740
But it's not true. They're all lies, James. Wicked lies.

01:01:33.420 --> 01:01:38.540
They only said these things, because I am a woman,

01:01:39.020 --> 01:01:40.400
and a Catholic.

01:01:41.460 --> 01:01:47.400
And they don't want a Catholic queen in Scotland. They

01:01:47.400 --> 01:01:49.920
want a Protestant king.

01:01:51.680 --> 01:01:59.020
A king like you, James. Why, James, my son, don't

01:01:59.020 --> 01:01:59.680
you help me?

01:02:01.060 --> 01:02:04.720
Why are you friendly with Elizabeth, my enemy?

01:02:05.940 --> 01:02:09.480
You don't want me back in Scotland, do you?

01:02:10.460 --> 01:02:13.920
You believe these lies, don't you?

01:02:15.220 --> 01:02:19.200
You talk to Moray and his friends every day.

01:02:20.540 --> 01:02:23.200
But they lied about me, James.

01:02:24.320 --> 01:02:30.860
Moray and his friends killed Riccio. They killed your father

01:02:30.860 --> 01:02:31.280
too.

01:02:32.000 --> 01:02:39.780
They stole my husband, Bothwell. Stole my son. Stole my

01:02:39.780 --> 01:02:40.700
son's love.

01:02:43.280 --> 01:02:50.480
I'm sorry, James. Forgive me. Sometimes I get very angry.

01:02:52.180 --> 01:02:58.740
It is difficult not to be angry when you are

01:02:58.740 --> 01:03:00.540
imprisoned for 20 years.

01:03:03.180 --> 01:03:08.980
Elizabeth didn't know what to do. Sometimes she believed Moray.

01:03:10.000 --> 01:03:16.340
Sometimes she didn't. She was afraid to kill me, because

01:03:16.340 --> 01:03:17.940
I was a queen.

01:03:19.320 --> 01:03:24.800
She was afraid to let me go free, because I

01:03:24.800 --> 01:03:26.300
have friends in England.

01:03:26.300 --> 01:03:32.720
The English Catholics want me to be queen of England,

01:03:33.700 --> 01:03:34.360
not her.

01:03:35.840 --> 01:03:40.440
And she is a woman with no husband and no

01:03:40.440 --> 01:03:43.820
son, so she hates me too.

01:03:45.660 --> 01:03:50.880
Sometimes the English Catholics write to me and ask me

01:03:50.880 --> 01:03:51.380
for help.

01:03:51.920 --> 01:03:59.640
And sometimes I write to them. Sometimes Elizabeth's men find

01:03:59.640 --> 01:04:00.680
these letters.

01:04:02.800 --> 01:04:06.980
The English Protestants want to kill me, because of these

01:04:06.980 --> 01:04:07.340
letters.

01:04:08.940 --> 01:04:14.760
You are a wicked woman, they say. You killed your

01:04:14.760 --> 01:04:16.080
husband, Darnley,

01:04:16.530 --> 01:04:21.180
and now you want to kill our queen, Elizabeth. You're

01:04:21.180 --> 01:04:22.220
going to die.

01:04:23.700 --> 01:04:29.760
I did not kill my husband, I said. And when

01:04:29.760 --> 01:04:33.480
I came to England, I did not want to kill

01:04:33.480 --> 01:04:34.220
your queen.

01:04:35.200 --> 01:04:40.360
I asked her for help. I wanted to go back

01:04:40.360 --> 01:04:41.140
to Scotland.

01:04:41.140 --> 01:04:47.400
But my Lord's, she put me in prison for 20

01:04:47.400 --> 01:04:48.140
years.

01:04:49.500 --> 01:04:55.840
20 years, my Lord's, I want to be free. Don't

01:04:55.840 --> 01:04:57.360
you understand that?

01:04:58.840 --> 01:05:02.520
When men write to me and try to help me,

01:05:03.200 --> 01:05:06.700
then yes, sometimes I write back.

01:05:07.680 --> 01:05:12.600
Why not? Is that wicked? Do you think?

01:05:16.240 --> 01:05:21.920
They didn't listen. Of course not. They want to kill

01:05:21.920 --> 01:05:22.220
me.

01:05:23.400 --> 01:05:29.700
And so they wrote to Queen Elizabeth. And now I

01:05:29.700 --> 01:05:32.600
sit here in Fotheringay Castle

01:05:33.440 --> 01:05:36.420
and wait for her to answer.

01:05:38.760 --> 01:05:44.200
I do not want to die James my son, but

01:05:44.200 --> 01:05:47.900
I do not want to live all my life in

01:05:47.900 --> 01:05:48.840
an English prison.

01:05:50.340 --> 01:05:53.840
I am old and tired of life.

01:05:55.540 --> 01:06:01.020
Think well of me, James, my son, and...

01:06:08.540 --> 01:06:21.160
I am old and tired of life in an English

01:06:21.160 --> 01:06:21.160
prison for 20 years.

01:06:21.180 --> 01:06:23.980
Chapter 9 A Death

01:06:26.160 --> 01:06:33.320
Queen Mary stopped writing then, yesterday afternoon, the 7th of

01:06:33.320 --> 01:06:35.280
February, 1587.

01:06:36.860 --> 01:06:42.760
We heard a horse outside our window. Mary looked out.

01:06:44.160 --> 01:06:48.060
There was a man there on the road from London.

01:06:49.440 --> 01:06:52.820
He had a letter from the Queen of England.

01:06:55.280 --> 01:07:00.620
In the evening, an Englishman, Lord Shrosbury came to see

01:07:00.620 --> 01:07:00.920
Mary.

01:07:03.140 --> 01:07:07.700
I am sorry, my lady, he said, but I have

01:07:07.700 --> 01:07:08.940
a letter from my Queen.

01:07:09.940 --> 01:07:13.200
You are going to die tomorrow.

01:07:15.820 --> 01:07:17.380
Mary did not move.

01:07:19.460 --> 01:07:26.400
When she asked quietly, at half past 8 in the

01:07:26.400 --> 01:07:31.980
morning, he said, I am very sorry, my lady.

01:07:33.800 --> 01:07:34.700
He went away.

01:07:37.160 --> 01:07:42.600
We did not sleep much that night. We talked and

01:07:42.600 --> 01:07:43.360
prayed to God,

01:07:43.360 --> 01:07:47.660
and she gave me her letter to her son, James.

01:07:50.180 --> 01:07:52.900
Give it to him, Bess, please.

01:07:54.600 --> 01:07:58.640
She said, and tell him how I died.

01:08:00.100 --> 01:08:02.800
Yes, my lady, I said.

01:08:04.340 --> 01:08:08.180
And so now I am going to tell you, King

01:08:08.180 --> 01:08:12.160
James, this is how your mother died.

01:08:13.920 --> 01:08:19.920
At six o'clock, she got up, prayed and dressed.

01:08:21.280 --> 01:08:26.520
She put on a red petticoat first, then a black

01:08:26.520 --> 01:08:30.480
dress and a white veil over the dress.

01:08:32.060 --> 01:08:37.940
The veil came from her head to her feet. She

01:08:37.940 --> 01:08:41.300
could see out through it, but we could not see

01:08:41.300 --> 01:08:41.820
her face.

01:08:43.360 --> 01:08:46.100
She looked like a woman on her wedding day.

01:08:49.160 --> 01:08:53.000
When the English men came, we went downstairs with her.

01:08:55.060 --> 01:08:59.880
Her little dog walked beside her under the veil, but

01:08:59.880 --> 01:09:01.420
the English men did not see that.

01:09:03.160 --> 01:09:06.320
Six of us went into a big room with her.

01:09:07.880 --> 01:09:10.560
A hundred people stood and watched.

01:09:11.800 --> 01:09:14.920
A Protestant churchman came to talk to her.

01:09:16.300 --> 01:09:21.240
My lady, he said, pray with me.

01:09:24.080 --> 01:09:30.460
No, she said, thank you, but no, I was born

01:09:30.460 --> 01:09:35.080
a Catholic, and I'm going to die a Catholic.

01:09:35.760 --> 01:09:38.940
I think God understands that.

01:09:41.280 --> 01:09:45.520
She prayed for five minutes and then stood up.

01:09:47.280 --> 01:09:49.960
The executioner came towards her.

01:09:51.480 --> 01:09:56.040
He was a big, strong man with an axe and

01:09:56.040 --> 01:09:57.780
something black over his face.

01:10:00.820 --> 01:10:05.620
I am sorry, my lady. He said, I don't hate

01:10:05.620 --> 01:10:09.940
you, but this is my work. Please forgive me.

01:10:11.940 --> 01:10:17.740
Of course, I forgive you. Mary said, I am old

01:10:17.740 --> 01:10:22.420
and tired, and you're going to open my

01:10:22.420 --> 01:10:27.220
prison doors for me. I am going to see God.

01:10:28.540 --> 01:10:30.240
Do your work well.

01:10:32.400 --> 01:10:35.440
Then she looked at me and her friends.

01:10:37.440 --> 01:10:44.780
Don't cry for me, ladies, she said. Please don't cry

01:10:44.780 --> 01:10:45.140
now.

01:10:47.760 --> 01:10:52.380
She could not walk to the block, so the executioner

01:10:52.380 --> 01:10:52.900
helped her.

01:10:54.720 --> 01:10:58.720
He took off her white veil and then he took

01:10:58.720 --> 01:11:02.240
off her black dress and put it on the floor.

01:11:03.900 --> 01:11:08.600
She stood there in her red petticoat with a smile

01:11:08.600 --> 01:11:09.400
on her face.

01:11:10.400 --> 01:11:17.360
Then the executioner put something over her eyes. Very slowly,

01:11:18.140 --> 01:11:20.800
Mary put her head on the block.

01:11:23.240 --> 01:11:29.440
The Lord, my God, is my one true friend. She

01:11:29.440 --> 01:11:35.720
said, I give my life, oh God, into your hands.

01:11:38.160 --> 01:11:48.540
Then the executioner lifted his axe once, twice, oh God,

01:11:49.200 --> 01:11:52.260
three times, and her head,

01:11:53.000 --> 01:11:59.580
her poor, poor head fell on the floor. It was

01:11:59.580 --> 01:12:02.180
very quiet in the room after that.

01:12:03.300 --> 01:12:09.120
It is a little thing ahead, a very little thing,

01:12:09.780 --> 01:12:12.380
but there was so much blood.

01:12:13.680 --> 01:12:18.900
Blood on her red petticoat, blood on her black dress

01:12:18.900 --> 01:12:32.160
and her white veil, blood on the executioner's

01:12:33.980 --> 01:12:37.040
face. We all looked and said nothing.

01:12:39.500 --> 01:12:43.260
The executioner put down his axe and stood quietly.

01:12:45.360 --> 01:12:49.220
And then Mary's little dog came out from under her

01:12:49.220 --> 01:12:52.900
bloody dress and veil and walked slowly,

01:12:53.940 --> 01:12:57.540
unhappily through the blood towards her head.

01:12:59.640 --> 01:13:04.200
My Lord, the story of your poor mother's life finishes

01:13:04.200 --> 01:13:04.820
here.

01:13:05.860 --> 01:13:11.780
We, her friends, cry for her, but that is how

01:13:11.780 --> 01:13:12.660
your mother died.

01:13:14.180 --> 01:13:19.960
She died like a queen, a good lady, and a

01:13:19.960 --> 01:13:20.900
famous queen.

01:13:22.900 --> 01:13:24.940
Mary, Queen of Scots.

